stop

public void stop()
Description copied from interface: ClipboardMonitor
Stops the monitoring of the clipboard. This method can be called multiple times. If the monitor has already been stopped, then the call has no effect.

Specified by:

run

public void run()
All user level methods must be called from the thread that will also poll the messages. Because Windows creates a message queue for each thread as soon as this thread creates a window or calls one of the message queue related functions.
